          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>half </strong>your <strong>ground cumin </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) with your <strong>ground coriander </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
